fields.description:
*Assessment*

If a Parameter has a property type of 'CommaDelimitedList', it causes CloudFormation to return a _InternalFailure_ error.

_Section of Cloudformation Template_

{code}
....
       "ClusterSize": {
            "Description":"Desired CoreOS Cluster Size",
            "Type":"Number",
            "NoEcho":"True"
        },

        "AvailZone": {
            "Description":"Availability Zone(s) for CoreOS Cluster deployment",
            "Type":"CommaDelimitedList",
            "NoEcho":"True"
        },
{code}

_Example of Error Returned_

{code}
# euform-create-stack --template-file cfn-coreos-as.json --parameter "CoreOSImageId=emi-2076F1DD" --parameter "UserKeyPair=account1-user01" --parameter "AcctId=408396244283" --parameter "ClusterSize=3" --parameter "AvailZone=ViciousLiesAndDangerousRumors,SirLuciousLeftFoot" CoreOSCluster --region account1-user01@
euform-create-stack: error (InternalFailure): null
{code}

*Details*

From the behavior, it seems that 'CommaDelimitedList' is not supported.  The error will show up even if the parameter is used in the template or not.  If the Parameter Type 'CommaDelimitedList' is not used, the Cloudformation template works just fine.

cfn-validate-template against AWS was used to validate the template:
{code}
$ cfn-validate-template --template-file cfn-coreos-as.json
PARAMETERS  ClusterSize    true  Desired CoreOS Cluster Size
PARAMETERS  UserKeyPair    true  User Key Pair
PARAMETERS  CoreOSImageId  true  CoreOS Image Id
PARAMETERS  AvailZone      true  Availability Zone(s) for CoreOS Cluster deployment
PARAMETERS  AcctId         true  IAM Account Id of User
{code}

*Signs*

