comments.body:
Any template with a parameter of type CommaDelimitedList should no longer cause an Internal Error.  If one wishes to reference the parameter in an Output, it is now considered an array, and an Fn::Join call should be made to see it.  For example

"Parameters: { 
  "MyParameter": {
    "Type": "CommaDelimitedList", 
    "Value": "1,2,3"
  }
}

...
Outputs: { 
  "MyOutput" : {
    "Value" : {"Fn::Join": [",", {"Ref":"MyParameter"}]}
  }
}

Should (and these snippets have not been vetted) show the values in the parameter separated by a comma.

I had to modify the template for my test environment as it was using VPC, just for reference the config is below.

